article.description: Nate Johnson had 21 points as Gardner-Webb beat Charleston Southern 83-74 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Gardner-Webb dumps Charleston Southern 83-74
article.story: NORTH CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Nate Johnson had 21 points as Gardner-Webb beat Charleston Southern 83-74 on Thursday night. Eric Jamison Jr. added 20 points for the Runnin' Bulldogs. Christian Turner had 17 points and seven assists for Gardner-Webb (14-15, 10-7 Big South Conference). Kareem Reid added 10 points and three blocks. Phlandrous Fleming Jr. had 23 points and six rebounds for the Buccaneers (13-16, 7-10). Ty Jones tied a career high with 23 points. Nate Louis had 12 points. The Runnin' Bulldogs leveled the season series against the Buccaneers with the win. Charleston Southern defeated Gardner-Webb 92-83 on Jan. 25. Gardner-Webb finishes out the regular season against Radford on the road on Saturday. Charleston Southern finishes out the regular season against Presbyterian on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
